{"title": "Shadow of the Rope", "description": "Rachel Minchin stands in the dock, accused of murdering the dissolute husband she was preparing to leave. The trial is sensational, and public opinion vehemently and almost universally against her. When the jury astonishes and outrages the world with a verdict of Not Guilty, Rachel quickly finds herself in need of protection. It comes in the form of a surprising offer of marriage from a mysterious stranger who has sat through every day of her trial. The marriage to this intriguing stranger, Mr. Steel, is by mutual agreement to be a platonic one, the only condition of which is that neither is ever to question the other about the past. The two travel to Steel\u2019s remote country estate, where Rachel accidentally discovers that her second husband\u2019s past was somehow intertwined with her first husband\u2019s history \u2013 but how, exactly, and why he determined to marry her, Steel will not say. As her doubts about her husband increase, local busybodies threaten to unearth Rachel\u2019s own past. And that is the least of the secrets that comes to light as this entertaining mystery unfolds. (Introduction by Christine Dufour)", "duration": 29686, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "1096", "name": "E. W. Hornung"}], "coverArt": "http://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt5/Shadow_of_the_Rope_1007.jpg", "copyright_year": "1902", "genres": ["Crime & Mystery Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Jacquerie"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Jacquerie"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Diana Majlinger"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "mim@can (1949-2017)"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Chapter I - The End of Their Life", "readers": [3967], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/shadow_ofthe_rope_1007_librivox/shadowoftherope_01_hornung_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1237}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter II - The Case for the Crown", "readers": [3967], "path": "http://www.